Eskom Stage 2 load shedding will continue today (Tuesday, 14 July) and will commence from 09:00 until 22:00. The areas affected will be: FROM 09:00 UNTIL 11:30 Mukondeni, Mashamba, Tshivhuyuni, Mulima, Nthabalala, Tshitale, Muwaweni, Mbhokota, Riverplats, Botlokwa and Soekmekaar. FROM 11:00 UNTIL 13:30 Malamulele areas, including Mangondi, Mulenzhe, Hlanganani areas, Masia, Majozi, Tiyani, Mahatlani, Bungeni, Basani, Nwamatatani, Olifantshoek, Masakona, Njhakajhaka, Nkuzana etc. and Giyani. FROM 13:00 UNTIL 15:30 Louis Trichardt, Levubu, Valdezia, Elim areas, Waterval, Chavani, Vleifontein, Ximausa, Blinkwater and Rotterdam, Mashau, Vuwani areas, Nesengani, Madombidzha areas and Sinthumule areas. FROM 15:00 UNTIL 17:30 Tshakhuma, Lwamondo, Shayandima, Muledane, Thohoyandou, Sibasa, Ngovhela, Phiphidi, Gondeni, Vhufuli, Vondwe, Makonde, Tshikweta Thengwe, Sanari, Makuya, Masisi, Malale, Madimbo, Muswodi etc. and all Mutale areas. THE FOLLOWING AREAS WILL NOT BE AFFECTED TODAY (14 JULY): MusinaÂ Town, Nancefield, Leeudraai, Tshipise Forever Resort, Pontdrif, Alldays , Soutpan, Bochum, and all Nzhelele villages.